#. quotes.js:338 quotes.js:341 quotes.js:344
msgid "Marcus Aurelius"
msgstr ""

#. desklet.js:35 quotes.js:15 quotes.js:225
msgid "Meditations, Book 5"
msgstr ""

#. desklet.js:161
msgid "Unknown"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:16
msgid "Waste no more time arguing about what a good man should be. Be one."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:18 quotes.js:333
msgid "Meditations, Book 10"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:19
msgid "If it is not right, do not do it; if it is not true, do not say it."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:21 quotes.js:51 quotes.js:213 quotes.js:345
msgid "Meditations, Book 12"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:22
msgid "The best revenge is not to be like your enemy."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:24 quotes.js:45 quotes.js:48 quotes.js:216
msgid "Meditations, Book 6"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:25
msgid "Loss is nothing else but change, and change is Nature's delight."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:27
msgid "Meditations, Book 9"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:28
msgid ""
"How much more grievous are the consequences of anger than the causes of it."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:30
msgid "Meditations, Book 11"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:31
msgid ""
"Never esteem anything as of advantage to you that will make you break your "
"word or lose your self-respect."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:33
msgid "Meditations, Book 3"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:34
msgid ""
"Do every act of your life as though it were the very last act of your life."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:36 quotes.js:57
msgid "Meditations, Book 2"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:37
msgid ""
"You have power over your mind, not outside events. Realize this, and you "
"will find strength."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:39 quotes.js:54 quotes.js:204 quotes.js:327 quotes.js:330
#. quotes.js:336 quotes.js:339 quotes.js:342
msgid "Meditations, Book 4"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:40
msgid ""
"Very little is needed to make a happy life; it is all within yourself, in "
"your way of thinking."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:42 quotes.js:60 quotes.js:63 quotes.js:207 quotes.js:210
#. quotes.js:219 quotes.js:222
msgid "Meditations, Book 7"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:43
msgid ""
"Accept the things to which fate binds you, and love the people with whom "
"fate brings you together."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:46
msgid ""
"The object of life is not to be on the side of the majority, but to escape "
"finding oneself in the ranks of the insane."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:49
msgid ""
"It is not death that a man should fear, but he should fear never beginning "
"to live."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:52
msgid "The happiness of your life depends upon the quality of your thoughts."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:55
msgid ""
"When you wake up in the morning, tell yourself: the people I deal with today "
"will be meddling, ungrateful, arrogant, dishonest, jealous and surly. They "
"are like this because they cannot tell good from evil. But I have seen the "
"beauty of good, and the ugliness of evil, and have recognized that the "
"wrongdoer has a nature related to my own."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:58
msgid ""
"Look back over the past, with its changing empires that rose and fell, and "
"you can foresee the future too. Its pattern will be the same, deviating only "
"in minor details. And to watch the mortal life of one man is to see them all."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:61
msgid ""
"Almost nothing material is needed for a happy life, for he who has "
"understood existence."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:64
msgid ""
"Make the best use of what is in your power, and take the rest as it happens."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:65 quotes.js:68 quotes.js:71 quotes.js:74 quotes.js:77
#. quotes.js:80 quotes.js:83 quotes.js:86 quotes.js:89 quotes.js:92
#. quotes.js:95 quotes.js:98 quotes.js:101 quotes.js:104 quotes.js:107
#. quotes.js:110 quotes.js:227 quotes.js:230 quotes.js:233 quotes.js:236
#. quotes.js:239 quotes.js:242 quotes.js:245 quotes.js:347 quotes.js:350
#. quotes.js:353 quotes.js:356
msgid "Epictetus"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:66
msgid "Enchiridion, I"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:67
msgid "No man is free who is not master of himself."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:69 quotes.js:231
msgid "Discourses, 2.1"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:70
msgid ""
"First say to yourself what you would be; and then do what you have to do."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:72
msgid "Discourses, 3.23"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:73
msgid ""
"If you want to improve, be content to be thought foolish and stupid with "
"regard to external things."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:75
msgid "Enchiridion, XIII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:76
msgid ""
"Freedom is not procured by a full enjoyment of what is desired, but by "
"controlling the desire."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:78
msgid "Discourses, 4.1"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:79
msgid ""
"People are disturbed not by things, but by the views which they take of "
"things."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:81 quotes.js:348
msgid "Enchiridion, V"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:82
msgid "Seek not the good in external things; seek it in yourself."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:84
msgid "Discourses, 3.24"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:85
msgid ""
"Never say about anything that I have lost it; but only that I have given it "
"back."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:87
msgid "Enchiridion, XI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:88
msgid ""
"Seek not for the things which happen as you wish; but wish the things which "
"happen to be as they are, and you will have a tranquil life."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:90
msgid "Enchiridion, VIII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:91
msgid ""
"Wealth consists not in having great possessions, but in having few wants."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:93 quotes.js:96 quotes.js:99 quotes.js:108 quotes.js:111
msgid "Discourses"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:94
msgid ""
"He is a wise man who does not grieve for the things which he has not, but "
"rejoices for those which he has."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:97
msgid "Don't explain your philosophy. Embody it."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:100
msgid ""
"We cannot choose our external circumstances, but we can always choose how we "
"respond to them."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:102
msgid "Enchiridion"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:103
msgid "First learn the meaning of what you say, and then speak."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:105
msgid "Discourses, 1.17"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:106
msgid ""
"You become what you give your attention to. If you yourself don't choose "
"what thoughts and images you expose yourself to, someone else will."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:109
msgid ""
"There is only one way to happiness and that is to cease worrying about "
"things which are beyond the power of our will."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:112
msgid "All things are foreign to us; time alone is ours."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:113 quotes.js:116 quotes.js:119 quotes.js:122 quotes.js:125
#. quotes.js:128 quotes.js:131 quotes.js:134 quotes.js:137 quotes.js:140
#. quotes.js:143 quotes.js:146 quotes.js:149 quotes.js:152 quotes.js:248
#. quotes.js:251 quotes.js:254 quotes.js:257 quotes.js:260 quotes.js:263
#. quotes.js:266 quotes.js:269 quotes.js:359 quotes.js:362 quotes.js:365
#. quotes.js:368 quotes.js:371 quotes.js:374
msgid "Seneca"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:114 quotes.js:117
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, I"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:115
msgid "While we are postponing, life speeds by."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:118
msgid ""
"It is not the man who has too little, but the man who craves more, that is "
"poor."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:120 quotes.js:144
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, II"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:121
msgid "Begin at once to live, and count each separate day as a separate life."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:123 quotes.js:372
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, CI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:124
msgid ""
"The greatest obstacle to living is expectancy, which hangs upon tomorrow and "
"loses today."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:126
msgid "On the Shortness of Life, IX"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:127
msgid "No man was ever wise by chance."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:129 quotes.js:363
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, LXXVI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:130
msgid ""
"Retire into yourself as much as you can; associate with those who are likely "
"to improve you."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:132
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, VII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:133
msgid "A happy life is one which is in accordance with its own nature."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:135
msgid "On the Happy Life, III"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:136
msgid "If you wish to be loved, love."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:138
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, IX"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:139
msgid "We suffer more often in imagination than in reality."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:141
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, XIII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:142
msgid "One who is everywhere is nowhere."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:145
msgid "To live is to fight."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:147
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, XCVI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:148
msgid "Luck is what happens when preparation meets opportunity."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:150
msgid "Epistulae Morales"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:151
msgid ""
"True happiness is to enjoy the present, without anxious dependence upon the "
"future, not to amuse ourselves with either hopes or fears but to rest "
"satisfied with what we have, which is sufficient."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:153
msgid "Letters from a Stoic"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:154
msgid "Better to trip with the feet than with the tongue."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:155 quotes.js:158 quotes.js:161 quotes.js:164 quotes.js:167
#. quotes.js:287 quotes.js:290
msgid "Zeno of Citium"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:156
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.26"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:157
msgid "The goal of life is to live in agreement with Nature."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:159
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.87"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:160
msgid ""
"We have two ears and one mouth, so that we should listen more than we say."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:162 quotes.js:165
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:163
msgid "Man conquers the world by conquering himself."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:166
msgid "All the good are friends of one another."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:168
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.32"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:169
msgid ""
"Lead me, Zeus, lead me, Destiny, wherever I have been assigned by you. I "
"will follow without hesitation; and if I am unwilling, because I am wicked, "
"I will follow nonetheless."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:170 quotes.js:173 quotes.js:176 quotes.js:284
msgid "Cleanthes"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:171 quotes.js:174
msgid "Hymn to Zeus"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:172
msgid ""
"All things are parts of one single system, which is called Nature; the "
"individual life is good when it is in harmony with Nature."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:175
msgid "Practice yourself in little things, and thence proceed to greater."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:177
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.168"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:178
msgid ""
"If you accomplish something good with hard work, the labor passes quickly, "
"but the good endures; if you do something shameful in pursuit of pleasure, "
"the pleasure passes quickly, but the shame endures."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:179 quotes.js:182 quotes.js:185 quotes.js:188 quotes.js:191
#. quotes.js:272 quotes.js:275 quotes.js:278 quotes.js:281
msgid "Musonius Rufus"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:180 quotes.js:279
msgid "Lectures, VI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:181
msgid ""
"We must not say that it befits only the philosopher to inquire how one ought "
"to live rightly; for philosophy is nothing else than this — the inquiry into "
"what is fitting and appropriate for a human being."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:183
msgid "Lectures, I"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:184
msgid ""
"Choose to die well while you can; wait too long, and it might become "
"impossible to do so."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:186
msgid "Lectures, VIII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:187
msgid ""
"The man who is truly good and wise neither struggles with adversity nor "
"complains of his lot; rather, he takes heart from even the harshest of "
"conditions."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:189
msgid "Lectures, X"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:190
msgid ""
"The philosopher's aim is not to hear many lectures and then fall silent, but "
"to live by those already heard."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:192 quotes.js:273
msgid "Lectures"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:193
msgid "If I had followed the multitude, I would not have studied philosophy."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:194 quotes.js:197 quotes.js:200 quotes.js:377
msgid "Chrysippus"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:195
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.183"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:196
msgid ""
"The virtues are interconnected; whoever truly possesses one virtue possesses "
"them all."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:198
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.125"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:199
msgid "No one is born a sage; goodness is an art which must be learned."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:201
msgid "Fragments"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:202
msgid "The universe is change; our life is what our thoughts make it."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:205
msgid ""
"Dwell on the beauty of life. Watch the stars, and see yourself running with "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:208
msgid "The art of living is more like wrestling than dancing."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:211
msgid ""
"Everything is but what your opinion makes it; and that opinion lies with "
"yourself."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:214
msgid "Adapt yourself to the things with which your lot has been cast."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:217
msgid "Confine yourself to the present."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:220
msgid ""
"Dig within. There lies the well-spring of good: ever dig, and it will ever "
"flow."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:223
msgid ""
"Such as are thy habitual thoughts, such also will be the character of thy "
"mind."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:226
msgid "Difficulties are things that show a person what they are."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:228
msgid "Discourses, 1.24"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:229
msgid "Only the educated are free."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:232
msgid "Know first who you are, and then adorn yourself accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:234
msgid "Discourses, 3.1"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:235
msgid "If you wish to be a writer, write; if you wish to be a reader, read."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:237 quotes.js:354
msgid "Discourses, 2.18"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:238
msgid ""
"When you close your doors and make darkness within, remember never to say "
"that you are alone, for you are not alone."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:240
msgid "Discourses, 1.14"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:241
msgid "Lameness is an impediment to the leg, but not to the will."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:243
msgid "Enchiridion, IX"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:244
msgid "It is impossible for a man to learn what he thinks he already knows."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:246
msgid "Discourses, 2.17"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:247
msgid ""
"It is not because things are difficult that we do not dare; it is because we "
"do not dare that they are difficult."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:249
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, CIV"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:250
msgid "Difficulties strengthen the mind, as labor does the body."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:252
msgid "On Providence, II"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:253
msgid "Sometimes even to live is an act of courage."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:255
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, LXXVIII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:256
msgid "There is no easy way from the earth to the stars."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:258
msgid "Hercules Furens"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:259
msgid "He suffers more than necessary, who suffers before it is necessary."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:261
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, XCVIII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:262
msgid "Wherever there is a human being, there is an opportunity for kindness."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:264
msgid "On the Happy Life"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:265
msgid ""
"If one does not know to which port one is sailing, no wind is favorable."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:267
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, LXXI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:268
msgid "The day which we fear as our last is but the birthday of eternity."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:270
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, CII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:271
msgid ""
"The most necessary part of philosophy is that which is put into practice."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:274
msgid ""
"Will not the educated woman be sensible? Yes; will not she be just? Of "
"course."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:276 quotes.js:282
msgid "Lectures, III"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:277
msgid ""
"The one who is to live well ought to learn beforehand the things that are "
"most necessary."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:280
msgid "Philosophical doctrine is of no use unless it leads the soul to virtue."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:283
msgid "Fate guides the willing, and drags the unwilling."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:285
msgid "Seneca, Letters from a Stoic, CVII"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:286
msgid "Happiness is a good flow of life."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:288
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.88"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:289
msgid "The way to attain virtue is to make a habit of self-mastery."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:291
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 7.24"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:292
msgid "No man steps in the same river twice."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:293 quotes.js:296 quotes.js:299 quotes.js:302
msgid "Heraclitus"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:294
msgid "Fragments, 49a"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:295
msgid "Character is destiny."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:297
msgid "Fragments, 119"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:298
msgid "Much learning does not teach understanding."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:300
msgid "Fragments, 40"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:301
msgid "The sun is new each day."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:303
msgid "Fragments, 6"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:304
msgid "I am a citizen of the world."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:305 quotes.js:308 quotes.js:311 quotes.js:314
msgid "Diogenes the Cynic"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:306
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 6.63"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:307
msgid ""
"It is the privilege of the gods to want nothing, and of godlike men to want "
"little."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:309
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 6.105"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:310
msgid "The most beautiful thing in the world is freedom of speech."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:312
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 6.69"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:313
msgid "The mob is the mother of tyrants."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:315
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 6.39"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:316
msgid "It is a royal thing to do good and be reviled."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:317
msgid "Antisthenes"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:318
msgid "Lives of the Eminent Philosophers, 6.3"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:319
msgid "I would rather have men ask why I have no statue than why I have one."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:320
msgid "Cato the Younger"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:321
msgid "Plutarch, Life of Cato the Younger"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:322
msgid ""
"We are each the center of a series of concentric circles — self, family, "
"neighbors, fellow citizens, humanity. The work is to draw the outer circles "
"toward the center."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:323
msgid "Hierocles"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:324
msgid "Elements of Ethics"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:325
msgid "Reject your sense of injury, and the injury itself disappears."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:328
msgid ""
"Be like the rocky promontory against which the restless surf continually "
"pounds."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:331
msgid ""
"Whatever happens to you has been waiting to happen since the beginning of "
"time."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:334
msgid "Time is a river of passing events; strong is its current."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:337
msgid "Do not act as if you had ten thousand years to live."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:340
msgid ""
"How much trouble he avoids who does not look to see what his neighbor says "
"or does."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:343
msgid ""
"Begin — to begin is half the work; let half still remain. Begin again, and "
"thou wilt have finished."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:346
msgid ""
"It is the act of an ill-instructed man to blame others; of one whose "
"instruction is beginning, to blame himself; of one whose instruction is "
"complete, to blame neither."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:349
msgid "All philosophy lies in two words: sustain and abstain."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:351
msgid "Fragment, via Aulus Gellius"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:352
msgid ""
"Don't let the force of an impression when it first hits you knock you off "
"your feet."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:355
msgid "There is nothing good or evil save in the will."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:357
msgid "Discourses, 3.10"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:358
msgid ""
"Every night ask yourself: what weakness did I overcome today? What virtue "
"did I acquire?"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:360
msgid "On Anger, III"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:361
msgid "As long as you live, keep learning how to live."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:364
msgid "It is a rough road that leads to the heights of greatness."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:366
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, LXXXIV"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:367
msgid ""
"Anger, if not restrained, is more hurtful to us than the injury that "
"provokes it."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:369
msgid "On Anger"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:370
msgid "Let us prepare our minds as if we had come to the very end of life."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:373
msgid ""
"Throw aside all hindrances and devote your time to the cultivation of a "
"sound mind."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:375
msgid "Letters from a Stoic, XVI"
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:376
msgid "All disturbances arise from false judgments."
msgstr ""

#. quotes.js:378
msgid "Plutarch, On Stoic Self-Contradictions"
msgstr ""

